    <worksheet name='4'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Bold'>GDP Growth Trend for BRICS Countries (2014–2023) </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
        <caption>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#0e0e0e' fontname='Tableau Medium' lmargin='225'>his stacked bar chart shows GDP growth trends for BRICS countries from 2014 to 2023. India and China consistently drove the group’s growth, with India recording the highest growth in 2023 at 8.15%. The impact of global disruptions is visible in 2020, where all nations experienced sharp declines. Brazil and South Africa displayed more volatility, while Russia’s growth showed notable fluctuation. This visualization highlights both the collective and individual trajectories of the BRICS economies across the last decade.t</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
