    <worksheet name='6'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Bold'>GDP Growth by Income Group (2014–2023) </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
        <caption>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#0e0e0e' fontname='Tableau Medium' lmargin='225'>This chart visualizes GDP growth trends across global income groups.</run>
            <run lmargin='225'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#0e0e0e' fontname='Tableau Medium' lmargin='225'>While all categories experienced a sharp decline in 2020 due to COVID-19, high-income countries rebounded the strongest, followed by gradual recovery among upper-middle and lower-middle income groups.</run>
            <run lmargin='225'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#0e0e0e' fontname='Tableau Medium' lmargin='225'>Low-income nations remained most vulnerable with slower post-pandemic recovery.</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Medium' lmargin='225'>Æ </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
