    <worksheet name='9'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Bold'>GDP Growth vs Unemployment Rate – Is There a Relationship? </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
        <caption>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Medium'>This scatter plot illustrates the inverse relationship between a country’s economic growth and unemployment rate, based on cross-country data post-COVID. The negative slope of the trend line confirms Okun’s Law, where stronger GDP performance generally aligns with lower unemployment. Outliers like South Africa and Sudan reveal structural job market challenges despite varying economic growth. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
