        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size sizing-mode='automatic' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='97898' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98518' x='741' y='1051'>
            <zone h='9198' id='3' type-v2='title' w='98518' x='741' y='1051' />
            <zone h='10381' id='4' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='98518' x='741' y='10249' />
            <zone h='78319' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='98518' x='741' y='20630'>
              <flipboard active-id='1' nav-type='arrowonly' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                <story-points>
                  <story-point captured-sheet='' id='1' />
                  <story-point captured-sheet='Global GDP Trends and Impacts ' id='2' />
                  <story-point captured-sheet='Unemployment vs GDP Growth: A Global Comparison Before and After the Pandemic ' id='3' />
                  <story-point captured-sheet='Economic Winners and Losers: Tracking Global GDP Growth Over the Years ' id='4' />
                  <story-point captured-sheet='Global Economic Shocks &amp; Sectoral Impacts' id='5' />
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='82641' id='6' story-point-id='1' type-v2='text' w='76705' x='11816' y='11424'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Medium' fontsize='12'>Agenda</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Medium' fontsize='12' underline='true'>Introduction</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Medium' fontsize='12'>Between 2014 and 2023, the global economy underwent significant shifts driven by financial crises, recovery efforts, and unprecedented disruptions such as the COVID-19 pandemic. This story explores the evolution of global GDP growth trends, unemployment patterns before and after the pandemic, and key insights across major economic groups like the G7 and BRICS nations. Through visual analytics, we highlight how countries and regions adapted to shocks, recovered, and positioned themselves for future economic resilience. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Medium' fontsize='12'>Slide 1: Global GDP Trends and Impacts</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Medium' fontsize='12'>Global GDP growth remained steady until 2019, but the COVID-19 pandemic triggered a historic contraction in 2020. Different income groups and G7 countries showed diverse recovery paths, highlighting resilience and structural challenges. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Medium' fontsize='12'>Slide 2: Unemployment vs GDP Growth Before and After the Pandemic</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Medium' fontsize='12'>Global unemployment rates surged after 2020. Countries with stronger GDP recoveries tended to manage unemployment better, though structural issues remained visible in certain regions. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Medium' fontsize='12'>Slide 3: G7 vs BRICS: Economic Winners and Losers</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Medium' fontsize='12'>Among G7 countries, recovery was moderate but consistent. BRICS countries displayed volatility, with India and China leading growth. Understanding these dynamics is key to forecasting future economic patterns. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Medium' fontsize='12'>Slide 4: Global Economic Shocks &amp; Sectoral Impacts</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Medium' fontsize='12'>This dashboard compares GDP impacts from World War II, the 2008 Financial Crisis, and COVID-19—highlighting the pandemic’s historic severity. It also visualizes how unemployment varied across global regions and shows sectoral vulnerability, with tourism- and manufacturing-dependent countries experiencing the deepest GDP declines during crises. This deeper context offers insight into how global shocks affect both macroeconomic indicators and sector-specific stability. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Medium' fontsize='12' underline='true'>Conclusion</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#4e79a7' fontname='Tableau Medium' fontsize='12'>The analysis reveals a clear disruption in global economic growth and employment between 2019 and 2021, with a sharp decline in 2020 due to COVID-19. Post-pandemic, most economies showed resilience, though recovery varied across income groups, regions, and individual countries. While nations like India and China demonstrated strong rebounds in GDP growth, challenges such as high unemployment persisted in regions like Africa and parts of Europe. Overall, the data underscores the importance of adaptive policies, strong health infrastructure, and global cooperation in building future economic stability </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{92F2D8B6-081A-4514-B6F8-ABBCD4B7E67C}' />
    </dashboard>
